metadata.title: Cessna 172
aws::graph::propositions: Cessna 172 Model Variants and Production Details
Cessna 172D was the 1963 model year.
Cessna 172D featured a cut down rear fuselage with a wraparound Omni-Vision rear window.
Cessna 172D featured a one-piece windshield.
Cessna 172D featured increased horizontal stabilizer span.
Cessna 172D featured a folding hat shelf in the rear cabin.
Cessna 172D's gross weight was increased to 2,300 lb (1,043 kg).
Cessna 172D's gross weight of 2,300 lb remained until the 172P model.
Cessna 172D added new rudder and brake pedals.
Cessna manufactured 1,011 units of the 172D model.
Reims Aviation in France produced 18 units of the F172D model.
F172D was the French-produced version of the Cessna 172D.
810 Cessna 172 aircraft were built.
Cessna 172E was the 1964 model year.
Cessna 172E featured a redesigned instrument panel with center-mounted avionics.
Cessna 172E replaced electrical fuses of previous models with circuit breakers.
Cessna manufactured 1,209 units of the 172E model.
Reims Aviation built 67 units as the F172E.
F172E was the French-produced version of the Cessna 172E.
Cessna 172F was the 1965 model year.
Cessna 172F featured electrically operated flaps.
Cessna 172F's electrically operated flaps replaced the previous lever-operated system.
Cessna 172F featured improved instrument lighting.
Cessna manufactured 1,400 units of the 172F model.
Reims Aviation produced 94 units as the F172F.
F172F was the French-produced version of the Cessna 172F.

text:
810 built.

172D

1963 model year with a cut down rear fuselage with a wraparound Omni-Vision rear window, a one-piece windshield, increased horizontal stabilizer span, and a folding hat shelf in the rear cabin.  Gross weight was increased to 2,300 lb (1,043 kg), where it would stay until the 172P.  New rudder and brake pedals were also added. 1,011 were built by Cessna, while a further 18 were produced by Reims Aviation in France as the F172D.

172E
1964 model year with a redesigned instrument panel with center-mounted avionics and circuit breakers replacing the electrical fuses of previous models. 1,209 built, 67 built by Reims as the F172E.

172F
1965 model year with electrically operated flaps to replace the previous lever-operated system and improved instrument lighting.  1,400 built, plus 94 by Reims as the F172F.
